Recently visited -Swarg Aashram. It is one of the preferred places we usually visit when we travel to Rishikesh.

Advantages-

1) It is near ram jhula and Gangaji Ghaat
2. They have a canteen but you will not get food at odd hours( they have specific timings for tea, breakfast and dinner)
3) Balcony and kitchen and fridge included
(it's perfect if you are travelling with family and want to cook food but you have to carry your utensils, induction and utensils soaps etc)
4) included living room- includes sofa and dining area.
5) it has a dressing area and wardrobe included (a separate almirah is provided in the living area)
6) park facility - where kids can play( even you will click pictures)
7)walking distance from Gangaji so changing clothes after a bath is easy as you will not get any changing place there.
8) market is nearby
9) Staff is polite and nice

Disadvantages -

1. Gates are open for the Aashram opened on 5 am and after 10 pm it's closed( you are not allowed to go outside)
2. They have fixed timings for food but if you are travelling with kids it will be sometimes difficult.

Note- 1) They have LIG, and MIG rooms available which include a kitchen and bathroom, and a balcony like a flat.
2) if you are a couple you must have a valid proof of your spouse without it you will not get a room.

According to legend, Lakshman crossed the river Ganges at this spot using a jute rope bridge, which was later replaced by a suspension bridge. The current Lakshman Jhula bridge is over 450 feet long and is one of the most popular tourist attractions in Rishikesh. The bridge offers stunning views of the river Ganges and the surrounding hills, and is surrounded by shops, restaurants, and ashrams. The area around Lakshman Jhula is also known for its spiritual significance, with many temples and ashrams located nearby.

Parmarth Niketan Ashram in Rishikesh is a serene and peaceful retreat nestled in the foothills of the Himalayas. The ashram is a perfect place to unwind and connect with your inner self. The accommodations are simple yet comfortable, with clean rooms that offer a basic but adequate level of amenities.

The ashram offers a range of spiritual and yoga programs, which are led by experienced and knowledgeable instructors. These programs are designed to help you deepen your practice and understanding of yoga, meditation, and spirituality. The ashram also offers daily Ganga Aarti, which is a beautiful and uplifting ceremony that takes place on the banks of the Ganges river.

The food served at the ashram is vegetarian and healthy, with a focus on locally sourced ingredients. The meals are simple but delicious, with a variety of dishes that cater to different dietary requirements. The dining hall is spacious and airy, with a peaceful ambiance that adds to the overall experience.

The ashram also offers various activities such as trekking, white water rafting, and cultural tours. These activities provide an opportunity to explore the natural beauty and cultural heritage of Rishikesh.

The staff at Parmarth Niketan Ashram are friendly and welcoming, always ready to assist with any needs or queries. The ashram also has a well-stocked library, which is a great resource for those interested in yoga and spirituality.

Overall, Parmarth Niketan Ashram in Rishikesh is a wonderful place to stay for anyone seeking a spiritual retreat or a break from the hustle and bustle of city life. The combination of yoga, meditation, healthy food, and serene surroundings make it an ideal destination for those seeking peace, tranquility, and inner growth.

featured_reviews.review_id:
My visit to Parmarth Niketan Ashram in Rishikesh was an unforgettable experience of self-discovery. Situated on the banks of the sacred Ganges, the temple offers a sea of   tranquility in which one can begin to transform within oneself.
When I entered
Parmarth Niketan, I was immediately surrounded by an atmosphere of peace. The Abbey's lush gardens with vibrant flowers and greenery create a harmonious environment that nourishes the mind, body and soul. The sound of the nearby river and the chirping of birds add to the relaxing atmosphere.
The Abbey offers a variety of accommodation options to suit all needs, from simple guest rooms to a range of luxury villas. Whichever you choose, guest rooms are clean, comfortable, thoughtful and convenient. It is a wonderful experience to appreciate the sounds of nature and the beauty of the Ganges.

Parmarth Niketan Ashram is known for spiritual classes, yoga and meditation, and lectures by spiritual leaders. Participation in these activities is transformative.
Yoga and meditation classes help me connect with my inner self and develop physical, mental and emotional balance. Spiritual teachings provide insight into ancient wisdom and practical advice for living a meaningful life. The daily Ganga Aarti ceremony at

Parmarth Niketan is a sight not to be missed. Praying to the holy Ganges on the banks of the temple with hundreds of devotees is a touching experience. Uplifting songs, air-filling light and spiritual satisfaction filled my heart with amazement.
The Abbey's beautiful surroundings offer many opportunities to connect with nature and find solace. Walking by the river, watching the sunrise or sunset on the Ganges, doing yoga in a peaceful place, these are moments of pure bliss. The ashram also organizes tours and excursions for tourists to explore the beauty of the Himalayas.

Parmarth Niketan Ashram's commitment to social and environmental issues is admirable. The ashram works on projects that protect the holy Ganges, promote education and provide medical care to the poor.
Engaging in service work is a humble experience that allows me to contribute to the advancement of society while maintaining my own compassion.

In conclusion, Parmarth Niketan Ashram is a place for those seeking spiritual understanding, inner peace and general wellness. From its peaceful location to supporting spiritual knowledge, this temple is a haven for the soul. Whether you are a spiritual seeker, a yoga lover or someone who needs a break from the stresses of everyday life, Parmarth Niketan Ashram will support and encourage you beyond your needs.

Rishikesh is a perfect blend of spirituality, adventure, and nature. As the "Yoga Capital of the World", the city offers a unique travel experience. The Ganga Aarti ceremony by the banks of the river Ganges was a spiritual highlight of my trip. I also enjoyed adventure activities such as river rafting and bungee jumping. Rishikesh is home to several yoga ashrams where visitors can learn and practice different types of yoga. I attended a yoga class and found it to be rejuvenating.

Overall, Rishikesh is a must-visit destination for anyone looking for a unique and enriching travel experience. It offers something for everyone, whether it's spirituality, adventure, or nature. The city's beauty and peacefulness left a lasting impression on me, and I can't wait to return.

After taking bath in Ganga in Haridwar, seeing Lord Neelkanth in Rishikesh and that unseen view of mountains leaves the mind calm and upbeat.
If you also go to Haridwar, then you must visit Lord Neelkanth.

There was a lot of discussion among us about seeing the Laxman Jhula after the darshan of Lord Neelkanth.
On asking some people nearby, they told that it is also a good place for tourists to visit.
After walking on the winding paths of the mountains for some time, we reached the place, which was still imaginary for us.

After walking some distance, now all of us had reached Laxman Jhoola. There was a bridge made of iron wires which was closed due to some reason at this time. The temple with a height of more than five storeys has been considered very famous in that area. The flow of 'Ganga ji' from under the bridge and the boat ride of people in the river is very enjoyable.
All of us could only go up to the four floors of the temple, but the sight of the flowing water from there was a delight to the mind.
If we all could reach the top of the temple, then maybe the limit of happiness would have been something else!!

 HAPPY JOURNEY
